<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-421-513  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 421 513.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  July 10 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>UK: Price Waterhouse issues warning on Friday 13th virus programs.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gold, Steve.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Price Waterhouse (information services).andO;Topic:     Computer virusesComputer CrimesData Security.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>UK: PRICE WATERHOUSE ISSUES WARNING ON FRIDAY 13TH VIRUS PROGRAMS LONDON,ENGLAND, 1990 JUL 07 (NB) -- Price Waterhouse, one of the UK's majormanagement consultancy groups, has issued a warning to computer users forFriday 13, which it says is a trigger date for the so-called Datacrime virusprogram.andM;&quot;Our research shows that the Datacrime virus, which was responsible for someof the last attacks on October 13, is still circulating,&quot; said PriceWaterhouse consultant David Frost, an acknowledged expert in data securitycircles, and the lead author of 'The Complete Computer Virus Handbook.'andM;Current research from Price Waterhouse indicates that the number of computervirus programs are escalating at around 500 percent annually.andP;  This figureexcludes the several new strains of previously recorded virus programs.andM;&quot;Users who take proper precautions will probably have very few problems onFriday 13, October 13 or any other time,&quot; said Frost, who added: &quot;An incidentwhich may look like a viral attack may be a harmless bug in the software.&quot;andM;(Steve Gold/19900707/Press andamp; Public Contact: David Frost, Price Waterhouse -Tel: 071-939-3000)</TEXT></DOC>